N2  - There is a strong tendency towards discriminative approaches in brain–computer interface (BCI)
research. We argue that generative model-based approaches are worth pursuing and propose a simple
generative model for the visual ERP-based BCI speller which incorporates prior knowledge about the
brain signals. We show that the proposed generative method needs less training data to reach a given
letter prediction performance than the state of the art discriminative approaches.
